The Human Rights Commission was also closely watching the Free State town of Senekal today as the EFF and various farming organistions gathered for the court appearance of two men accused of the murder of farm manager Brendin Horner. To discuss this further, Sally Burdett spoke to Human rights Commissioner Jonas Sibanyoni. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema and his supporters are in hot water again, this time with the SA Human Rights Commission. The Freedom Front Plus has lodged a complaint after EFF supporters sang 'Kill the Boer' in Senekal. READ: Senekal murder case: Tensions high outside court In video footage, they're heard singing the song as they protest at the magistrate's court in the Free State. FF Plus leader Pieter Groenewald says it was time action was taken against Malema in the interests of everyone in the country. The FF Plus succeeded in having the song declared hate speech in 2003.